1
00:01:31,370 --> 00:01:34,950
[Unbreakable Ⅱ]

2
00:01:35,380 --> 00:01:37,800
[Episode 21]

3
00:01:38,479 --> 00:01:41,000
Besides, this all happened 10 years ago,

4
00:01:41,250 --> 00:01:43,810
and since they were minors, it can't really be considered a crime.

5
00:01:44,280 --> 00:01:46,680
Both Civil Law and the Minor Protection Law

6
00:01:46,700 --> 00:01:48,420
focus on evidence and the statute of limitations.

7
00:01:48,690 --> 00:01:49,770
Most importantly,

8
00:01:49,840 --> 00:01:50,750
the consequences it had

9
00:01:50,780 --> 00:01:52,400
for Xiao Nannan

10
00:01:52,400 --> 00:01:54,250
haven't shown up in any real way.

11
00:01:54,430 --> 00:01:56,320
It's hard to measure

12
00:01:56,350 --> 00:01:59,190
emotional and mental harm in a lawsuit.

13
00:02:01,120 --> 00:02:02,540
I can't believe that

14
00:02:03,640 --> 00:02:05,280
something like this, involving so many people,

15
00:02:05,600 --> 00:02:07,310
can't be dealt with by the law.

16
00:02:07,590 --> 00:02:08,590
The law doesn't punish the majority;

17
00:02:09,210 --> 00:02:10,930
I still find it difficult to fire a lawsuit.

18
00:02:13,430 --> 00:02:13,980
What about you?

19
00:02:16,460 --> 00:02:18,210
I think what Qiu Hua said makes sense.

20
00:02:18,470 --> 00:02:19,300
Let's just wait and see.

21
00:02:19,410 --> 00:02:20,579
We need to know what Xiao Nannan's

22
00:02:20,600 --> 00:02:21,560
asking for today;

23
00:02:21,590 --> 00:02:23,120
does she want to go to court, or what?

24
00:02:23,120 --> 00:02:24,010
Let's figure that out first.

25
00:02:28,380 --> 00:02:30,990
Qiu Hua's right about this. I know about it already;

26
00:02:31,240 --> 00:02:32,260
no need for you to tell me.

27
00:02:35,340 --> 00:02:36,250
Did I say something wrong?

28
00:02:36,400 --> 00:02:38,030
It seems like everything you said was wrong.

29
00:02:39,260 --> 00:02:40,300
She asked me that, though.

30
00:02:42,350 --> 00:02:43,720
Ms. Xiao, Mr. Yang,

31
00:02:45,900 --> 00:02:47,900
we'd like to know

32
00:02:48,079 --> 00:02:50,240
what your real request is today.

33
00:02:50,320 --> 00:02:53,829
Are you looking for legal punishment

34
00:02:54,180 --> 00:02:56,270
for those who hurt you back then?

35
00:02:56,300 --> 00:02:57,900
No, no.

36
00:02:58,110 --> 00:03:00,650
I didn't mean to punish them.

37
00:03:02,030 --> 00:03:04,230
So, what's the purpose of you coming to us?

38
00:03:06,510 --> 00:03:08,250
He suggested that

39
00:03:08,280 --> 00:03:09,550
I seek legal help

40
00:03:10,490 --> 00:03:11,750
and ask them for an apology.

41
00:03:11,770 --> 00:03:12,270
Yes.

42
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:13,870
It was my suggestion.

43
00:03:14,070 --> 00:03:16,180
They treated Nannan so cruelly back then,

44
00:03:16,520 --> 00:03:17,880
and changed her forever.

45
00:03:18,170 --> 00:03:20,079
Even if they don't face legal punishment,

46
00:03:20,400 --> 00:03:21,800
they should at least

47
00:03:21,960 --> 00:03:23,010
apologize to her.

48
00:03:23,700 --> 00:03:26,350
I believe if Nannan receives an apology from them,

49
00:03:27,430 --> 00:03:29,030
she might slowly begin to heal

50
00:03:29,640 --> 00:03:30,730
from the shadows of that time.

51
00:03:31,050 --> 00:03:32,840
An apology alone seems too easy for them.

52
00:03:37,870 --> 00:03:39,680
The harm caused by school bullying

53
00:03:39,940 --> 00:03:41,740
is indeed huge

54
00:03:41,770 --> 00:03:42,790
for teenagers,

55
00:03:43,240 --> 00:03:45,360
but figuring out how to punish it

56
00:03:45,390 --> 00:03:47,480
is a big challenge for society.

57
00:03:47,760 --> 00:03:50,079
It can't all be regulated by law.

58
00:03:52,020 --> 00:03:54,090
From today's conversation,

59
00:03:54,520 --> 00:03:55,590
it seems like

60
00:03:55,590 --> 00:03:57,800
your career is going well

61
00:03:58,270 --> 00:03:59,940
and you've built a new life for yourself.

62
00:04:00,400 --> 00:04:01,870
However, those things from the past

63
00:04:01,870 --> 00:04:03,520
have clearly left a deep scar

64
00:04:03,540 --> 00:04:05,070
in your heart.

65
00:04:07,150 --> 00:04:08,020
I just

66
00:04:08,050 --> 00:04:10,630
want to confirm with you again.

67
00:04:11,400 --> 00:04:13,630
What you really want

68
00:04:13,630 --> 00:04:14,960
is a sincere apology from them

69
00:04:15,050 --> 00:04:17,120
so that you can move past the shadow

70
00:04:17,149 --> 00:04:18,000
of what happened back then.

71
00:04:18,720 --> 00:04:19,950
This is more important to you

72
00:04:19,950 --> 00:04:22,040
than them facing legal punishment,

73
00:04:22,130 --> 00:04:23,060
right?

74
00:04:23,090 --> 00:04:24,570
Yes, Ms. Luo.

75
00:04:24,590 --> 00:04:25,840
That's what I mean.

76
00:04:30,190 --> 00:04:30,840
Xia Shu,

77
00:04:31,450 --> 00:04:33,010
how's the case going

78
00:04:33,190 --> 00:04:34,360
on your end?

79
00:04:34,600 --> 00:04:35,870
I'm almost done.

80
00:04:35,990 --> 00:04:36,960
I have time.

81
00:04:37,570 --> 00:04:38,200
Ms. Luo,

82
00:04:39,500 --> 00:04:41,080
are you suggesting that

83
00:04:41,110 --> 00:04:42,950
Ms. Xia take charge of this matter?

84
00:04:44,820 --> 00:04:45,659
Mr. Chen,

85
00:04:45,690 --> 00:04:49,060
let's discuss the case of our firm first, shall we?

86
00:04:49,080 --> 00:04:49,880
Hold on.

87
00:04:54,409 --> 00:04:55,850
Ms. Xiao,

88
00:04:56,270 --> 00:04:57,890
we are willing to

89
00:04:57,920 --> 00:04:59,310
provide legal assistance,

90
00:04:59,600 --> 00:05:01,500
but we'll need to sign an agreement first.

91
00:05:02,310 --> 00:05:03,220
Your case

92
00:05:03,240 --> 00:05:05,320
will be led by Xia Shu,

93
00:05:05,510 --> 00:05:06,670
and both Qiu Hua and I

94
00:05:06,690 --> 00:05:08,750
will assist with the work.

95
00:05:09,310 --> 00:05:10,870
First, we need to

96
00:05:10,870 --> 00:05:12,310
conduct an investigation,

97
00:05:12,390 --> 00:05:14,750
and gather evidence regarding the bullying that happened to you.

98
00:05:15,090 --> 00:05:17,170
Then we'll see what we should do next.

99
00:05:17,200 --> 00:05:17,750
Okay?

100
00:05:19,750 --> 00:05:20,480
Xia Shu,

101
00:05:20,510 --> 00:05:22,540
you can discuss the details of the agreement with them.

102
00:05:22,570 --> 00:05:23,090
Okay.

103
00:05:23,810 --> 00:05:25,370
Please follow me.

104
00:05:25,400 --> 00:05:26,060
Xia Shu.

105
00:05:26,190 --> 00:05:28,420
I'll get the agreement for you.

106
00:05:28,730 --> 00:05:29,270
Thank you.

107
00:05:36,720 --> 00:05:38,240
Go ahead, Mr. Chen. What's up?

108
00:05:38,750 --> 00:05:39,600
Let's step outside and talk.

109
00:05:43,430 --> 00:05:44,240
What's going on?

110
00:05:44,430 --> 00:05:45,430
What do you mean?

111
00:05:46,920 --> 00:05:48,120
Aren't you handling this case?

112
00:05:48,240 --> 00:05:49,680
Didn't I tell you, Xia Shu will handle this.

113
00:05:49,700 --> 00:05:50,800
You know better than anyone else

114
00:05:50,800 --> 00:05:51,600
about Xia Shu's work ability.

115
00:05:51,600 --> 00:05:53,950
It's unreliable to let her handle the case.

116
00:05:54,950 --> 00:05:56,950
That's why I asked Qiu Hua for help.

117
00:05:56,950 --> 00:05:58,720
Why didn't you listen to me carefully?

118
00:05:58,720 --> 00:05:59,510
I heard it clearly.

119
00:05:59,510 --> 00:06:00,480
But I introduced this case,

120
00:06:00,480 --> 00:06:01,920
and you want me to cooperate with others?

121
00:06:04,600 --> 00:06:05,510
Let us do it.

122
00:06:05,530 --> 00:06:07,360
We're close and we can communicate, right?

123
00:06:10,160 --> 00:06:10,690
We...

124
00:06:10,720 --> 00:06:11,450
Yes.

125
00:06:19,270 --> 00:06:20,070
Have you forgotten?

126
00:06:20,070 --> 00:06:20,990
What did I forget?

127
00:06:23,010 --> 00:06:24,410
Mr. Xu's case

128
00:06:24,900 --> 00:06:26,060
is also handled by our firm.

129
00:06:26,610 --> 00:06:27,800
I have to keep an eye on it.

130
00:06:29,360 --> 00:06:30,190
Don't worry.

131
00:06:30,390 --> 00:06:32,070
If you need any help,

132
00:06:32,150 --> 00:06:32,930
I'm always here.

133
00:06:40,909 --> 00:06:42,670
What does Mr. Xu have to do with me?

134
00:06:45,750 --> 00:06:47,280
Fang Rui, let's go.

135
00:06:47,630 --> 00:06:48,560
Take my clothes.

136
00:06:55,070 --> 00:06:56,380
We're leaving, Ms. Qiu, Ms. Xia.

137
00:06:56,560 --> 00:06:56,940
Bye bye.

138
00:06:56,970 --> 00:06:57,610
Bye bye.

139
00:07:01,750 --> 00:07:03,160
Don't get discouraged.

140
00:07:03,240 --> 00:07:05,040
If this girl were too easy to pursue, it wouldn't be interesting,

141
00:07:05,060 --> 00:07:05,500
right?

142
00:07:06,160 --> 00:07:07,160
At this stage,

143
00:07:07,340 --> 00:07:08,580
the more anxious you get, the less anxious she'll be.

144
00:07:09,160 --> 00:07:10,800
Let me tell you, the less anxious you are...

145
00:07:10,820 --> 00:07:11,620
Mr. Chen.

146
00:07:12,710 --> 00:07:14,000
Mr. Chen.

147
00:07:14,040 --> 00:07:16,230
I've been waiting for you for so long.

148
00:07:16,230 --> 00:07:17,270
What's up, Mr. Han?

149
00:07:18,040 --> 00:07:20,480
Do you still remember you have a case?

150
00:07:20,830 --> 00:07:22,160
I have more than one case.

151
00:07:22,160 --> 00:07:22,990
Which one are you talking about?

152
00:07:23,920 --> 00:07:25,160
Great minds have short memories.

153
00:07:25,240 --> 00:07:26,310
Let me remind you—

154
00:07:26,870 --> 00:07:27,490
Mingshan.

155
00:07:31,270 --> 00:07:33,240
Yesterday was the deadline for Minghai Group's appeal, right?

156
00:07:33,240 --> 00:07:33,630
Yes.

157
00:07:33,960 --> 00:07:34,760
I forgot to ask.

158
00:07:34,790 --> 00:07:35,650
I'll contact the judge now...

159
00:07:35,680 --> 00:07:36,430
No, no, no.

160
00:07:36,450 --> 00:07:38,690
Let me handle this little thing.

161
00:07:38,720 --> 00:07:39,690
I've already called.

162
00:07:40,400 --> 00:07:41,480
Minghai Group didn't appeal.

163
00:07:41,630 --> 00:07:43,190
Then that means the judgment is final.

164
00:07:43,190 --> 00:07:43,630
Yes.

165
00:07:43,630 --> 00:07:44,800
We can start the enforcement process immediately.

166
00:07:44,800 --> 00:07:45,920
That's good news for us.

167
00:07:46,190 --> 00:07:47,560
Don't be happy too soon.

168
00:07:47,830 --> 00:07:48,800
Shouldn't Mingshan Group

169
00:07:48,970 --> 00:07:51,090
be more active about this than you?

170
00:07:51,120 --> 00:07:51,650
Yes.

171
00:07:52,030 --> 00:07:53,510
But has Mingshan Group reached out to you?

172
00:07:55,010 --> 00:07:56,450
No.

173
00:07:56,530 --> 00:07:57,880
Why hasn't Mingshan Group reached out to you?

174
00:07:57,900 --> 00:07:58,610
Have you thought about it?

175
00:07:59,000 --> 00:08:01,240
You should really keep your guard up.

176
00:08:01,820 --> 00:08:03,020
That makes sense.

177
00:08:03,930 --> 00:08:05,290
Then let's go to Mingshan Group together.

178
00:08:05,310 --> 00:08:07,340
No, I just got back.

179
00:08:07,370 --> 00:08:08,680
I haven't even had a sip of water.

180
00:08:09,000 --> 00:08:09,750
Okay.

181
00:08:09,750 --> 00:08:10,950
You've done a great job, Mr. Han.

182
00:08:10,950 --> 00:08:11,800
I can go by myself.

183
00:08:11,800 --> 00:08:12,480
Fang Rui,

184
00:08:12,870 --> 00:08:13,870
let's go.

185
00:08:13,870 --> 00:08:14,430
Okay.

186
00:08:14,430 --> 00:08:15,120
We're leaving, Mr. Han.

187
00:08:15,120 --> 00:08:16,190
Okay, bye bye.

188
00:08:16,230 --> 00:08:18,260
How could I forget such an important thing?

189
00:08:19,310 --> 00:08:19,890
Well...

190
00:08:20,570 --> 00:08:21,360
Mr. Han.

191
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:23,040
Mentor, wait for me.

192
00:08:31,240 --> 00:08:33,400
You mean Mingshan Group hasn't asked about it?

193
00:08:34,669 --> 00:08:35,480
Yes.

194
00:08:36,200 --> 00:08:37,150
They didn't give a call

195
00:08:37,280 --> 00:08:38,650
after they won the case.

196
00:08:41,549 --> 00:08:42,220
Han,

197
00:08:44,480 --> 00:08:45,550
in this situation,

198
00:08:46,870 --> 00:08:47,700
when they lose the case,

199
00:08:48,200 --> 00:08:50,390
Mingshan Group is more anxious than anyone.

200
00:08:51,510 --> 00:08:52,370
But once they win,

201
00:08:52,770 --> 00:08:54,640
they don't care, while everyone else is worried.

202
00:08:56,390 --> 00:08:57,430
You have to be careful.

203
00:08:58,330 --> 00:08:59,170
Don't worry.

204
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:01,580
Their little tricks

205
00:09:01,600 --> 00:09:03,270
can't fool me.

206
00:09:03,270 --> 00:09:04,510
I'm keeping an eye on everything.

207
00:09:04,890 --> 00:09:06,080
Who are you keeping an eye on?

208
00:09:09,840 --> 00:09:12,100
All the interested parties.

209
00:09:13,590 --> 00:09:15,760
I have more than one set of eyes watching—

210
00:09:15,790 --> 00:09:17,100
actually, several.

211
00:09:17,630 --> 00:09:19,840
As soon as there's a sign of movement on their side,

212
00:09:20,120 --> 00:09:21,260
I'll know immediately.

213
00:09:21,870 --> 00:09:22,600
No.

214
00:09:23,720 --> 00:09:26,360
You have to pay special attention to your partner, Chen Shuo.

215
00:09:34,150 --> 00:09:38,070
You mean Chen Shuo might betray the firm

216
00:09:38,150 --> 00:09:39,870
for personal gain?

217
00:09:41,030 --> 00:09:41,750
No.

218
00:09:42,600 --> 00:09:44,910
I'm afraid he'll be blinded by money,

219
00:09:45,510 --> 00:09:47,510
not being flexible where he needs to be,

220
00:09:47,810 --> 00:09:49,900
only focusing on his own interests,

221
00:09:50,190 --> 00:09:53,000
and end up causing even more damage to the firm.

222
00:09:53,030 --> 00:09:53,860
Understand?

223
00:09:55,090 --> 00:09:56,180
Don't worry.

224
00:09:57,940 --> 00:09:59,670
He might act slick,

225
00:10:00,110 --> 00:10:02,210
but he's just a rookie in front of me.

226
00:10:05,270 --> 00:10:07,570
But there's something I need to mention.

227
00:10:08,950 --> 00:10:11,470
It's I who's keeping an eye on this case

228
00:10:12,320 --> 00:10:14,960
but I can only get 20% of the agency fee.

229
00:10:15,910 --> 00:10:17,790
Can you find another lawyer

230
00:10:17,910 --> 00:10:20,080
in our firm

231
00:10:20,100 --> 00:10:21,370
as self-sacrificing as me?

232
00:10:22,790 --> 00:10:23,910
Come on, Han.

233
00:10:24,870 --> 00:10:27,170
Don't pretend to be good after taking advantage.

234
00:10:27,700 --> 00:10:29,580
You're just keeping an eye on it.

235
00:10:30,140 --> 00:10:32,360
This case was handled by Chen Shuo himself.

236
00:10:33,390 --> 00:10:35,870
20% is not bad.

237
00:10:39,360 --> 00:10:41,150
The new ones are always more appealing.

238
00:10:43,550 --> 00:10:46,360
No matter how much effort the old hands put in, they don't get the same credit.

239
00:10:59,790 --> 00:11:00,460
It's me.

240
00:11:00,840 --> 00:11:02,320
Let me ask you something.

241
00:11:02,840 --> 00:11:04,750
Do you know why

242
00:11:04,750 --> 00:11:06,230
Minghai Group didn't appeal?

243
00:11:08,900 --> 00:11:10,230
[Mingshan]

244
00:11:13,810 --> 00:11:15,130
Mr. Sun, we've been waiting for you.

245
00:11:15,550 --> 00:11:17,200
Sorry, sorry.

246
00:11:17,200 --> 00:11:19,030
I've had meetings all day,

247
00:11:19,030 --> 00:11:20,550
and now I need to rush to another one.

248
00:11:21,180 --> 00:11:22,250
Let me update you on the situation.

249
00:11:22,480 --> 00:11:23,720
I've confirmed with the court that

250
00:11:23,720 --> 00:11:24,710
Minghai Group didn't appeal,

251
00:11:24,740 --> 00:11:25,750
and the judgment has already taken effect.

252
00:11:25,750 --> 00:11:27,410
Can we now proceed with enforcement?

253
00:11:27,870 --> 00:11:28,950
I'll follow your lead.

254
00:11:30,480 --> 00:11:32,150
Considering the other party's background

255
00:11:32,360 --> 00:11:33,800
and the nature of their business,

256
00:11:34,150 --> 00:11:35,240
apart from freezing

257
00:11:35,240 --> 00:11:36,600
their bank accounts,

258
00:11:36,600 --> 00:11:37,840
I think we should also investigate

259
00:11:37,840 --> 00:11:39,820
their non-core business assets

260
00:11:39,920 --> 00:11:41,440
and report any financial information to the court.

261
00:11:41,440 --> 00:11:42,200
What do you think?

262
00:11:42,240 --> 00:11:44,280
I'll leave everything to you two.

263
00:11:44,480 --> 00:11:45,220
Please.

264
00:11:45,600 --> 00:11:46,960
Sorry, I have to rush to another meeting.

265
00:11:46,960 --> 00:11:48,630
Hurry up. Sorry.

266
00:11:52,150 --> 00:11:52,910
Keep in touch, Mr. Sun.

267
00:11:52,910 --> 00:11:53,910
Okay.

268
00:11:55,750 --> 00:11:56,200
Let's go.

269
00:12:03,370 --> 00:12:04,130
Wait, Mentor.

270
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:06,000
This is his business.

271
00:12:06,020 --> 00:12:07,450
Why doesn't he pay any attention to it?

272
00:12:08,790 --> 00:12:10,120
You can't teach an old dog new tricks.

273
00:12:10,120 --> 00:12:12,310
He must be playing tricks behind my back.

274
00:12:16,190 --> 00:12:18,040
Xue, help me investigate something.

275
00:12:19,480 --> 00:12:20,030
Mentor,

276
00:12:21,080 --> 00:12:22,080
I have a classmate

277
00:12:22,200 --> 00:12:23,680
who's currently working as a lawyer at Deren Law Firm.

278
00:12:23,870 --> 00:12:26,050
They just took on the Minghai Group's case.

279
00:12:26,240 --> 00:12:27,510
So if needed,

280
00:12:27,510 --> 00:12:28,630
I can ask them

281
00:12:28,630 --> 00:12:30,240
and see if Minghai Group has had any contact

282
00:12:30,240 --> 00:12:31,630
with Mingshan Group recently.

283
00:12:32,200 --> 00:12:33,000
It's impossible,

284
00:12:33,000 --> 00:12:34,430
since they're representing Minghai Group.

285
00:12:34,670 --> 00:12:35,410
